BRAND VOICE
Character: A fashion editor who dresses for herself, not for trends. Confident, selective, never loud. 
Voice Element Rule Tone Editorial, self-assured, slightly minimal SL Short. One idea per sentence. No run-ons. Punctuation Minimal. Dashes over parentheses. No exclamation points. Vocabulary (use) curated, elevated, intentional, drop, season, worn, considered Vocabulary (never) affordable, budget, cheap, sale, hurry, limited time, don't miss RA "you" — direct. Never "our customers" or "everyone" Never sounds like mass market, fast fashion, salesy, desperate 
**Brand voice in 3 adjectives:** Editorial Selective Minimal 
